OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1780138973
OL,3,CTributes paid to 'proud' D-Day veteran
OL,4,CAlec Penstone following death aged 101
OL,6,FTributes have been paid to a D-Day
OL,7,Fveteran who has died at the age of 101.
OL,9,FAlec Penstone, who lived on the Isle
OL,10,Fof Wight and was a submarine detector
OL,11,Fon HMS Campania, stopping U-boats on D-
OL,12,FDay, died on Thursday (28 May).
OL,14,FIn a statement, the Royal Naval
OL,15,FAssociation (RNA) said: "A proud
OL,16,Fwartime veteran, Alec lived an
OL,17,Fextraordinary life of courage, service
OL,18,Fand resilience, and leaves behind a
OL,19,Flegacy that will never be forgotten.
OL,26,@wD@YOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/11
