PN,41402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1780138973
OL,3,CTributes paid to 'proud' D-Day veteran
OL,4,CAlec Penstone following death aged 101
OL,6,F"Alec was just 15 years old when war
OL,7,Fbroke out. As the blitz devastated
OL,8,FLondon, he volunteered as a part-time
OL,9,Fair raid precautions messenger,
OL,10,Fserving throughout 1940 and 1941.
OL,12,F"Reflecting on those difficult days,
OL,13,FAlec once said: 'At 15 years of age,
OL,14,Fpulling bodies out of bombed
OL,15,Fbuildings, you grow up very quickly.'
OL,17,F"As soon as he was old enough, Alec
OL,18,Fjoined the Royal Navy."
OL,26,@yD@AOUzD@WO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/11
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1780138973
OL,3,CTributes paid to 'proud' D-Day veteran
OL,4,CAlec Penstone following death aged 101
OL,6,FThe association reported Mr Penstone
OL,7,Fas saying: "My mates were all going
OL,8,Fup, joining up, and I decided that I
OL,9,Fdon't want to stay there any longer. I
OL,10,Fwent and joined the Royal Navy, as a
OL,11,FHO (hydrographic officer), and that
OL,12,Fwas the start of it."
OL,14,FThe RNA's statement added: "Alec
OL,15,Fserved aboard HMS Campania, an escort
OL,16,Faircraft carrier tasked with sweeping
OL,17,Ffor mines and hunting U-boats.
OL,26,@oD@LOUtD@UO]vD@\OU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/11
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1780138973
OL,3,CTributes paid to 'proud' D-Day veteran
OL,4,CAlec Penstone following death aged 101
OL,6,F"Much of his service was spent three
OL,7,Fdecks below on constant action
OL,8,Fstations, listening for torpedoes,
OL,9,Fmines and enemy submarines in the
OL,10,Funforgiving conditions of the Atlantic
OL,11,Fand Arctic seas.
OL,13,F"He went on to complete 10 Arctic
OL,14,Fconvoys, returning home forever shaped
OL,15,Fby the experience and sacrifice of war.
OL,17,F"As a nation, we owe our today to
OL,18,Fveterans like Alec.
OL,26,@uD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/11
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1780138973
OL,3,CTributes paid to 'proud' D-Day veteran
OL,4,CAlec Penstone following death aged 101
OL,6,F"The Royal Naval Association was
OL,7,Fhonoured to count him among our
OL,8,Fbeloved members and shipmates, and we
OL,9,Fremember him with immense pride,
OL,10,Fgratitude and affection.
OL,12,F"Fair winds and following seas,
OL,13,FShipmate Alec."
OL,15,FSpeaking to ITV News Meridian in 2023,
OL,16,FMr Penstone described the role he
OL,17,Fplayed in D-Day.
OL,26,@uD@OO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/11
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1780138973
OL,3,CTributes paid to 'proud' D-Day veteran
OL,4,CAlec Penstone following death aged 101
OL,6,FHe said: "In the early hours of 6 June
OL,7,Fall hell broke loose. I was 27 feet
OL,8,Fdown beneath the waterline and the
OL,9,Fonly communication I had with the
OL,10,Fbridge was a telephone.
OL,12,F"And we heard then that it was an
OL,13,Finvasion and we were going over to
OL,14,FNormandy.
OL,16,F"We were the cover force protecting
OL,17,Fthe invading craft from the U-Boats.
OL,18,FWe were kept quite busy. We were
OL,19,FAction Stations for nearly 40 hours.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/11
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1780138973
OL,3,CTributes paid to 'proud' D-Day veteran
OL,4,CAlec Penstone following death aged 101
OL,6,F"Without us there would have been a
OL,7,Fmassacre. We weren't the only ships
OL,8,Fdoing it."
OL,10,FCaptain Bill Oliphant, chief executive
OL,11,Fof the RNA, said: "We are deeply
OL,12,Fsaddened to hear of Alec's passing.
OL,13,FAlec represented the very best of his
OL,14,Fgeneration: courageous, resilient and
OL,15,Ffull of life. He was a true legend,
OL,16,Fand the Royal Naval Association will
OL,17,Fhonour and remember him always."
OL,26,@sD@SOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/11
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
